snippet.textDisplay:
Please beware.
This magnetic sister likely allows sharing it off sideways, which for me and a visually identical magnetic connector probably put +12V (quick charge) on what's supposed to be GND and GND on a data pin.
That phone's USB data pin circuitry is so fried, that it doesn't even recognize any charger anymore. It only trickle charges in the mode the hardware uses to recover from zero remaining charge and being turned off.

There is a different layout with 5 pins staggered in two rows, similar to a serial port connector, which is sensitive about the direction (like microUSB, not fancy USB-C) but doesn't stuffed from the shearing issue.
